 <br>
People that want go on these raids must obtain good Magic, Fire and Cold resistance gear.  Magic resistance un-buffed should be 50 or more; Cold or Fire (depending on the dragon) resistance un-buffed should close to 100. You can borrow it, or better still buy jewelry from enchanters or loot it off dead MOBs.   <br>
<br>
Raiding Vox and Naggy are training ground raids for the high-end Planes/Level 65 mobs raids. If we are going to be able do these as a guild, there has to be a very serious, long-term commitment of time and efforts from a large number of guild people having toons in the 40-52 level range.  <br>
<br>
For folks that have their main in this range, these raids most likely will be the first time you spend 2-4 hours mostly sitting in one place, getting no loot, negative experience, and seeing a large number of competent people get killed because one person makes a mistake.  <br>
<br>
For higher level, the commitment is also hard; you have to take time off from hunting with you main, doing what you do best and act as leader, buffer, mother hen, teacher or harder still, level-up and learn to play an “uber twink alt” in a critical skill (warrior, rogue, cleric, enchanter, or bard) class for use on these raids.  <br>
<br>
To do this as a guild we have to learn to organize quickly.  Vox and Naggy spawn is 7 days or when the server resets.   Unlike plane raids that have 3-4 weeks to get your RL and toon organized, these raids only have at most 7 days (more likely 24 hours) to say “Yes, me and 20-40 other people are going show up somewhere in 2-3 hour window equipped and ready do what it takes to kill the dragon!” n. b.  Doing Ragefire for the cleric epics are also going to require this level of organization/mobilization on an ever shorter warning period.    <br>
<br>
If we can’t (and it’s not bad if we can’t) as a guild commit to doing that, we need to better develop our existing networks of friends in other groups or guilds so that our members can find and get help if they &quot;need&quot; the loot from these mobs.  <br>
